o	Performance time (run time) of each analyzer tool, the average and what tail times look like
Collateral 
A collateral manager poses the following questions after limited review of Tavant’s functionality. A combo of presentation and demo may be appropriate to get into this level of discussion: 

Functionality
•	Can the system read non-UAD compliant valuation forms?
•	Is there functionality that allows a user to indicate they are ready for the next review, and does the system leverage appraisal, loan, and property information to assign the next priority review to the user?
•	Can more than one user work on a review, such as Preflight, Analyst, Escalated Reviewer, ROV, or Repurchase Analyst? Can more than one worksheet or set of conditions be leveraged by the various levels of review? 
•	They indicated that they can import the SSR and appraisal data from the UCDP. Can they also obtain the risk scores, alerts, and messaging? Can they do this for FHA and VA appraisals as well
Risk Management
•	How is Tavant ensuring they will be ready for the new UAD?
•	Is there the ability to assign risk ratings to reviews based on appraisal, property, or GSE risk scores, alerts, and data, which could be leveraged for review assignment and contents? 
•	Will Tavant interact with LADs 2.0? What controls are in place to ensure that the user who clears conditions and/or the product has the appropriate authority?
Workflow and Automation
•	If the appraisal data cannot be captured from the UCDP, can the appraisal review be placed on hold until it is available to ensure the most efficient processing?
•	Will Tavant leverage loan-level data that may change after the appraisal is delivered to assign review priority? For example, if the anticipated closing/funding date changes.
•	Is there workflow functionality within Tavant that would push the review to the next level reviewer or type of review (e.g., ROV) based on a user’s attributes or loan/property attributes? Or does the user have to manually find a review?
I am confirming our ability / appetite to send over our collateral checklist; as well as vendor management RFI.
